#!/bin/sh
#
# Configured as part of the DigitalOcean 1-Click Image build process

cat <<EOF
********************************************************************************

Welcome to DigitalOcean's One-Click OpenCode Droplet.

OpenCode is an open-source AI coding agent that runs in your terminal. Use
natural language to write, debug, and refactor code. It supports multiple
LLM providers (Claude, GPT, Gemini, and more) and works with Models.dev
for free model access.

GETTING STARTED:

1. Configure your LLM provider (required):
   Visit https://opencode.ai/auth for free models, or add your API key.
   See docs: https://opencode.ai/docs

2. Run OpenCode:
   cd /path/to/your/project
   opencode

Helper Commands:
  Check version:  /opt/opencode-version.sh
  Update:         /opt/update-opencode.sh

Configuration:  /root/.config/opencode/
Getting started: cat /root/opencode_info.txt

For full documentation: https://opencode.ai/docs

********************************************************************************
To delete this message of the day: rm -rf $(readlink -f ${0})
EOF
